    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-06-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-06-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="495"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d495">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">310.2/6–2154</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Representative at the United Nations</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lodge</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Assistant Secretary of State for united
                        Nations Affairs</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_KEYDMK1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Key</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-06-21">June 21,
                            1954</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear <persName corresp="#p_KEYDMK1">David</persName>
                    </hi>: In reply to yours of June 16th, I think there can be no question at all
                    that the President at his meeting with <persName corresp="#p_CHURCHILLWSSWA1"
                        >Churchill</persName> and <pb facs="0761" n="733" xml:id="pg_733"/>
                    <persName corresp="#p_EDENA1">Eden</persName> should come to an agreement on not
                    having the Chinese representation question come up at the United Nations. I
                    cannot conceive of anything which is more important for them to agree on.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry Cabot Lodge, Jr.</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
